ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course represents your opportunity to pursue original mathematics research for Yale credit. If this is an attractive idea to you, sign up; if this is something you wouldn't like, walk on by. Your experience in the course will be determined entirely by your relationship with your advisor and his/her project, so it is to you to pick a good advisor with a good project. Here, as always I suppose, "good" is subjective, and it can mean a lot of things, like, "intriguing," "fun," "rewarding," "gripping your interest until the wee hours of the morning," and so on.
This was a great course, I don't know if it will be taught again, but I think that it could lead to a very productive collaboration between an interested member of the English department and Michael.
